00:35:10.220 --> 00:35:13.774
So I do love that story
and you can check it out.

00:35:13.774 --> 00:35:14.857
It is online.

00:35:17.007 --> 00:35:19.840
So Dr. King said that he had dream

00:35:21.042 --> 00:35:22.709
that his four little
children would one day live

00:35:22.709 --> 00:35:24.377
in a world where they were not judged

00:35:24.377 --> 00:35:26.399
by the color of their skin

00:35:26.399 --> 00:35:29.482
but by the content of their character

00:35:30.418 --> 00:35:33.638
and I think The Lanterman
Act really for people

00:35:33.638 --> 00:35:35.325
with intellectual and
developmental disabilities

00:35:35.325 --> 00:35:39.492
in California certainly was the
launch of that kind of idea.

00:35:40.778 --> 00:35:44.759
That people would be
looked at as people first.

00:35:44.759 --> 00:35:46.713
So I wanted to take a moment

00:35:46.713 --> 00:35:48.571
before I delve in The Lanterman Act

00:35:48.571 --> 00:35:52.071
to just talk about identity and disability

00:35:52.970 --> 00:35:55.155
and the importance of language.

00:35:55.155 --> 00:35:59.754
I'm not really, language
probably not a good to say.

00:35:59.754 --> 00:36:02.337
I'm not really a stickler on language.

00:36:02.337 --> 00:36:05.806
I would like behavior and
actions to really speak louder

00:36:05.806 --> 00:36:08.586
than language but in this case.

00:36:08.586 --> 00:36:12.367
It really made an impression
on me as I learn people

00:36:12.367 --> 00:36:13.968
first language and the difference

00:36:13.968 --> 00:36:18.210
between saying a disabled
person or a autistic person

00:36:18.210 --> 00:36:22.380
and a person with autism or
person with a disability.

00:36:22.380 --> 00:36:24.140
The importance here is
it sets the individual

00:36:24.140 --> 00:36:25.461
and the individual's identity,

00:36:25.461 --> 00:36:28.378
this core of explaining themselves.

00:36:29.873 --> 00:36:34.582
And so it's a change from
saying that the adjective,

00:36:34.582 --> 00:36:37.642
the modifier is the important
thing about the person.

00:36:37.642 --> 00:36:40.361
That they're defined by their deficits

00:36:40.361 --> 00:36:43.134
and it moves it to
saying I'm a human being

00:36:43.134 --> 00:36:46.707
that whatever challenges I have in life.

00:36:46.707 --> 00:36:48.764
And whatever special gifts and talents

00:36:48.764 --> 00:36:50.561
that informs my identity

00:36:50.561 --> 00:36:53.926
but that's not the sum
total of my identity.

00:36:53.926 --> 00:36:57.941
People don't say I'm a
glasses wearing person.

00:36:57.941 --> 00:37:00.330
It's like a person who wears glasses

00:37:00.330 --> 00:37:03.080
so that's really important to me.

00:37:05.894 --> 00:37:09.009
It connects to the Dr.
King quote that it's about

00:37:09.009 --> 00:37:12.983
the individual's identity
and we all know this.

00:37:12.983 --> 00:37:14.351
The more you work with an individual,

00:37:14.351 --> 00:37:17.566
the less you see them
as your first impression

00:37:17.566 --> 00:37:19.574
and the more you see them as sort of

00:37:19.574 --> 00:37:22.625
the core identity of who they are.

00:37:22.625 --> 00:37:24.748
That's informed by their life's experience

00:37:24.748 --> 00:37:27.748
and sometimes by their disabilities.

00:37:29.450 --> 00:37:32.292
So I wanna go a little bit deeper

00:37:32.292 --> 00:37:34.292
into The Lanterman Act Promise.

00:37:34.292 --> 00:37:36.329
It's really the promise of equal access

00:37:36.329 --> 00:37:38.423
against the promise of support.

00:37:38.423 --> 00:37:40.095
People hear the word entitlement

00:37:40.095 --> 00:37:42.280
and they think of preference
and preferential treatment

00:37:42.280 --> 00:37:44.212
and it's important to bring them back

00:37:44.212 --> 00:37:46.117
really to a civil rights frame for me.

00:37:46.117 --> 00:37:47.924
And say it's about equal access.

00:37:47.924 --> 00:37:49.543
It's about leveling the playing field.

00:37:49.543 --> 00:37:52.791
It's about letting people
live, work and play

00:37:52.791 --> 00:37:55.622
and have an access to that as people

00:37:55.622 --> 00:37:57.900
without disabilities have access to it.

00:37:57.900 --> 00:38:01.150
It's not about any special "treatment".

00:38:04.390 --> 00:38:06.892
I'm gonna move, I think
quickly through these slides

00:38:06.892 --> 00:38:10.778
somewhat but the first
page of The Lanterman Act

00:38:10.778 --> 00:38:13.954
is like a declaration of
independence for the country.

00:38:13.954 --> 00:38:15.761
It's really well written.

00:38:15.761 --> 00:38:18.481
Art Bolton was a staffer
for Frank Lanterman

00:38:18.481 --> 00:38:21.518
and others but Art
really played a huge role

00:38:21.518 --> 00:38:23.884
in drafting this language.

00:38:23.884 --> 00:38:25.733
And it says right at the beginning that

00:38:25.733 --> 00:38:28.237
"The State of California
accepts a responsibility

00:38:28.237 --> 00:38:30.239
"for persons with
developmental disabilities

00:38:30.239 --> 00:38:35.055
"and an obligation to them
that it must discharge."

00:38:35.055 --> 00:38:37.696
It affects hundreds of
thousands of children and adults

00:38:37.696 --> 00:38:40.008
directly and I love this part,

00:38:40.008 --> 00:38:42.624
and having an important
impact on the lives

00:38:42.624 --> 00:38:45.531
of their families, neighbors
and entire communities.

00:38:45.531 --> 00:38:48.017
Developmental disabilities
presents social, medical,

00:38:48.017 --> 00:38:51.233
economic, legal I would say issues now.

00:38:51.233 --> 00:38:55.316
They said problems in 1969
of extreme importance.

00:38:56.948 --> 00:38:58.698
So what it really do?

00:39:00.761 --> 00:39:03.397
All of this is contained
again in that first page

00:39:03.397 --> 00:39:04.318
of The Lanterman Act.

00:39:04.318 --> 00:39:08.318
The first 4501 of welfare
and institutions code.

00:39:09.759 --> 00:39:12.024
It created an entitlement.

00:39:12.024 --> 00:39:15.613
The entitlement really got rolling in 1985

00:39:15.613 --> 00:39:18.946
when the Arc of California sued the DDS.

00:39:20.946 --> 00:39:23.789
Brought a case that went
to the state supreme court.

00:39:23.789 --> 00:39:27.956
In 1985, state supreme court
decision basically says yes.

00:39:30.037 --> 00:39:32.855
That obligation means
you have an obligation

00:39:32.855 --> 00:39:37.484
both to fund the system and if
the system runs out of money.

00:39:37.484 --> 00:39:38.917
Then the Department of
Developmental Services,

00:39:38.917 --> 00:39:40.573
Shelton's gonna go back to the legislature

00:39:40.573 --> 00:39:42.352
and ask for more money.

00:39:42.352 --> 00:39:44.740
When it runs out of money
that was the original intent

00:39:44.740 --> 00:39:46.639
in the supreme court decision

00:39:46.639 --> 00:39:49.891
and that the Department
of Development Services

00:39:49.891 --> 00:39:54.157
would have some limited
influence on regional centers.

00:39:54.157 --> 00:39:56.640
At the service level, the IPP,

00:39:56.640 --> 00:39:59.881
the individual program
plan Shelton reference

00:39:59.881 --> 00:40:03.277
would be the driver of services
and the regional centers

00:40:03.277 --> 00:40:06.263
would be responsible to their communities

00:40:06.263 --> 00:40:08.556
to provide services in a way

00:40:08.556 --> 00:40:11.329
that best met those needs of the IPP.

00:40:11.329 --> 00:40:12.981
And the Department of
Developmental Services

00:40:12.981 --> 00:40:15.804
will play a funding role and a legal role

00:40:15.804 --> 00:40:19.194
but direct regional centers in what to do.

00:40:19.194 --> 00:40:21.447
And that really is where the flexibility

00:40:21.447 --> 00:40:23.141
in the system has come from

00:40:23.141 --> 00:40:25.278
and the ability to innovate in a way

00:40:25.278 --> 00:40:27.875
that we could never done over 50 years

00:40:27.875 --> 00:40:32.640
if we were state owned and
operated, no offense Shelton.

00:40:32.640 --> 00:40:35.640
(audience laughing)

00:40:36.932 --> 00:40:41.099
It also established the IPP
which is one of my mentors

00:40:43.403 --> 00:40:44.987
who's passed away last year,

00:40:44.987 --> 00:40:47.800
Barbara Maizie of Contra Costa ARC.

00:40:47.800 --> 00:40:52.268
Just hammered about the IPP
being the legal source document.

00:40:52.268 --> 00:40:56.102
It all comes from the IPP but it's true.

00:40:56.102 --> 00:40:59.161
That's how we plan one person at a time

00:40:59.161 --> 00:41:02.320
and don't have cookie cutter
one size fits all services.

00:41:02.320 --> 00:41:06.128
We have services that are
responsive to the individual.

00:41:06.128 --> 00:41:10.811
The other things Lanterman
Act right away does is

00:41:10.811 --> 00:41:14.341
have this great language
around establishing

00:41:14.341 --> 00:41:17.959
an array of services
based on needs and choices

00:41:17.959 --> 00:41:19.718
and that will be regardless of age.

00:41:19.718 --> 00:41:22.083
And regardless of degree of disability

00:41:22.083 --> 00:41:25.577
which is a very important
thing and sometimes

00:41:25.577 --> 00:41:27.370
gets in the way when
we're trying to explain

00:41:27.370 --> 00:41:30.139
to legislatures especially
new legislatures

00:41:30.139 --> 00:41:32.165
and give them an idea
of the people we serve.

00:41:32.165 --> 00:41:35.538
It's really helpful to
bring a vast variety

00:41:35.538 --> 00:41:37.962
of the people we serve because it's hard

00:41:37.962 --> 00:41:40.042
if you haven't had an
experience of intellectual

00:41:40.042 --> 00:41:42.003
and developmental
disabilities in your family

00:41:42.003 --> 00:41:44.517
or neighborhood or friends.

00:41:44.517 --> 00:41:48.684
To really be able to talk
about just the vast diversity

00:41:50.323 --> 00:41:54.490
in difference and presenting
needs and different ways

00:41:56.121 --> 00:41:59.719
of communicating is represented
by the people we serve.

00:41:59.719 --> 00:42:01.564
And then this great phase of integration

00:42:01.564 --> 00:42:03.594
into the main stream
life of the community.

00:42:03.594 --> 00:42:07.415
Who knew the community
even had a mainstream life.

00:42:07.415 --> 00:42:11.165
But it does and we're
still chasing that goal

00:42:14.476 --> 00:42:17.909
and then another phrase
that's an awesome phrase

00:42:17.909 --> 00:42:20.700
is that and again, relates
to the equal access

00:42:20.700 --> 00:42:22.958
not preferential treatment.

00:42:22.958 --> 00:42:26.883
The whole system is to help
people with intellectual

00:42:26.883 --> 00:42:28.331
and developmental disabilities approximate

00:42:28.331 --> 00:42:30.630
the patterns of everyday living available

00:42:30.630 --> 00:42:32.357
to people without disabilities,

00:42:32.357 --> 00:42:33.606
and now we're seeing that language

00:42:33.606 --> 00:42:36.106
echoed in the ACBS final rule.

00:42:38.420 --> 00:42:42.305
The new federal expectations
or current federal expectations

00:42:42.305 --> 00:42:43.751
that we have to comply with,

00:42:43.751 --> 00:42:47.626
that all the country has to
comply with by March of 2019.

00:42:47.626 --> 00:42:51.417
But right there in The Lanterman Act

00:42:51.417 --> 00:42:55.982
and this great phrase
we really wanna pursue.

00:42:55.982 --> 00:42:58.499
We're not pursuing them,
they're coming to us.

00:42:58.499 --> 00:43:01.735
We really wanna help people pursue

00:43:01.735 --> 00:43:04.622
their own personal futures.

00:43:04.622 --> 00:43:07.224
And for me I always like to think of

00:43:07.224 --> 00:43:09.385
that as we're here to help people

00:43:09.385 --> 00:43:12.543
have equal access by meeting their needs

00:43:12.543 --> 00:43:17.030
but also by helping them define
and meet their aspirations.

00:43:17.030 --> 00:43:19.561
It's not just all about sort of

00:43:19.561 --> 00:43:22.123
Maslow's lowest levels of meeting needs.

00:43:22.123 --> 00:43:23.952
It's also higher level of aspirations

00:43:23.952 --> 00:43:27.619
so we are charged with
supporting people in.

