00:45:52.845 --> 00:45:55.038
Who didn't come from the field

00:45:55.038 --> 00:45:57.192
and said why you keep saying medical model

00:45:57.192 --> 00:45:58.288
like it's a negative thing.

00:45:58.288 --> 00:46:02.585
We in medicine think medical
model kind of make sense

00:46:02.585 --> 00:46:03.877
but for people with disabilities,

00:46:03.877 --> 00:46:05.486
the medical model really translated

00:46:05.486 --> 00:46:09.645
into a disempowering model in our history.

00:46:09.645 --> 00:46:13.742
Where the physician would
diagnose that the person

00:46:13.742 --> 00:46:16.142
was basically broken and needed to be fix

00:46:16.142 --> 00:46:19.456
in various different ways
and would prescribe things

00:46:19.456 --> 00:46:22.539
to help them get better and fix them.

00:46:24.398 --> 00:46:27.481
But what's even more kind of damaging

00:46:28.723 --> 00:46:31.862
was that we as human service professionals

00:46:31.862 --> 00:46:34.757
took on this quasi medical model.

00:46:34.757 --> 00:46:36.808
Where we were diagnosing

00:46:36.808 --> 00:46:40.975
that if Eric just would bathe
more, Eric would be better

00:46:42.615 --> 00:46:45.771
regardless of what Eric wanted to do.

00:46:45.771 --> 00:46:50.428
And so we kind of diagnosed
folks in the early days

00:46:50.428 --> 00:46:52.385
about what they needed to get a job

00:46:52.385 --> 00:46:55.248
in the community, for instance.

00:46:55.248 --> 00:46:58.940
Not only was disempowering
and rob people of their agency

00:46:58.940 --> 00:47:01.374
but it also wasn't effective.

00:47:01.374 --> 00:47:05.392
We had folks who would
have to be in workshops

00:47:05.392 --> 00:47:08.339
